    <text>
        <body>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>June 6 1854</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Revd Sir. </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I enclose the proceedings of<lb/> the Congregation Shearith Israel,
                at a Meeting<lb/> held on <date>4th</date> inst. for publication in your<lb/>
                <sic>invalueable</sic> Occident.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The interest you have always<lb/> felt in the proceedings of the
                various Conrega-<lb/>tions, induces this Congregation to forward the<lb/> same to
                you, in order to show, that notwith-<lb/>standing all efforts used, particularly in
                this<lb/> City, to ridicule the Orthodox Congregations,<lb/> &amp; to destroy our
                sacred Religion, Shearith<lb/> Israel is in a flourishing condition, and<lb/>
                enabled to contribute to the establishment<lb/> of an Orthodox Synagogue. Trusting
                that<lb/> He, whose hand has always been <sic>outstreched</sic><lb/> over
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>, will still continue <add>to</add> do so, to<lb/>
                those who trust in the God of <persName>Abraham</persName>, and<lb/> adhere to
                ancient landmarks of Judaism.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With my best wishes for your prospe-<lb/>rity, I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Revd Sir yr obt Sr</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">B Paleature<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Secty K K S. I.</p>
